    {
      "id": "0d698661c413a5431ebe8f31e546e3e903c26ef2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-31 16:07:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nHuh? I think the entire point of starting MGS first then OSTs was so that MDS will start and be able to connect to all OSTs.\n\nWhy would MDT erase any config on MGS at all? That sounds like a different problem that needs to be solved differently I think.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6aba43634e3a1422cc13dd6d0a4a438f422ea5cb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-01 07:12:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI also doubted this in bug 24050 comment #30, #48, #51, #57 and got a partial answer from Johann in comment #55. I think the fix of lustre_start utility was just a workaround, not fixing the Lustre issue. Lustre really supported the starting order of MGS->OST->MDT before. So, Hongchao, could you please investigate this? We need figure out the real issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "59020529230eb2d1e86d5085796c6b64a1f71a4e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-03 23:25:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe comment in bugzilla indicates that this order only needs to happen on first mount which I guess I can believe even though it is still somewhat strange that first MDT connect would wipe config data.\n\nPerhaps we just need to incorporate a real mount in MGS->MDT->OST) order in our formatting scripts instead?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
